The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	 Paris: Mahesh Bhupathi of India and Max Mirnyi of Belarus won their eighth title by defeating the unseeded pair of Mark Knowles of the Bahamas and Andy Ram of Israel 7-5, 7-5, in the Paris Masters final, Sunday.    
	In the singles, Robin Soderling of Sweden won his first Masters 1000 title by beating Gael Monfils of France 6-1, 7-6 (1). He became the first Swede to win a Masters 1000 tournament since Thomas Enqvist in 2000 at Cincinnati. He will leapfrog Andy Murray of Britain to rise to a career-high No. 4 in the rankings.         
	 Calcutta: Ankeet Kashyap of Assam beat fourth seed, Vanshal DSouza of Maharashtra 6-3, 3-6 ,6-4 to qualify for the main draw of boys singles U-14 at the Aita Junior tennis championship series, being played at Shambazar Tennis Club. Others to qualify for the main draw were Upamanyu Sinha of Gujarat, Jaffer Javed, Ritwik Chatterjee, Vikash Singh, Ishaan Tibrewal, Md. Adnan Ali and Vicky Mashi.         
	 Abu Dhabi: In a run up to the AFC Asian Cup 2011, India suffered yet another heavy defeat at the hands of Kuwait in an international friendly, here on Sunday. The West Asian giants defeated India 9-1. Al Azraq pumped in three goals in the opening half. Kuwait went on to score six goals in the second half to record. Mohammed Rafi scored a consolation goal for India in the 69th minute.         
	 Madrid: A moment of genius from Lionel Messi led to a 3-1 home win for Barcelona over Villarreal in La Liga, on Saturday, that put the champions two points clear of arch-rivals Real Madrid at the top of the standings. With the two sides locked at 1-1 after first-half goals from Barca striker David Villa and his Villarreal counterpart Nilmar, the Argentina forward showed why he is the World Player of the Year with a finish of breathtaking skill in the 58th minute.         
	Calcutta: Sreetama Biswas beat Sreeja Majumdar 11-8, 11-8 in the Nursey girls final of the Childrens Day Table Tennis Championship, organised by the Dakshin Kalikata Sevasram ,under the guidance of the BTTA.    
	Other winners: Nursery boys: Gobindo Mondal, Cadet girls: Ananya Chakraborty, Cadet Boys: Abhishek Attalani, Sub-junior girls: Anushka Shamanta, sub-junior boys: Sayantan Chatterjee.         
	Calcutta: St Thomas Church School beat South Point High School by 27 runs, in the final of the U-16 category of the 8th Inter School T20 cricket tournament, organised by Sloba Cricket Coaching Camp at St. Lawrence School Ground, Sunday.    
	Brief scores: St Thomas Church School 144/5 in 20 ovs, South Point High School 117/8 in 20 ovs. St Thomas Church School won by 27 runs.        
	 Kanpur: Praveen Kumar will be tying the knot with childhood sweetheart Sapna, in Meerut, on Thursday.                                                                                                                                                       
